Oh sweet-soulful-gentle Mia,
you were the absolute sweetest.
You gifted us with purely unconditional love, fierce loyalty, and blissful joy for 11 glorious years. Since the second we first saw you, you were perfect, and you remained perfect…minute after minute…day after day…year after year. 
In 11 short years, you filled us up with lifetimes of infinite love. 
We will always carry you in our hearts and souls. Thank you, sweet Mia, thank you for finding us.
Thank you for making our family complete. Thank you.  Forever grateful.

Last night we gathered to put a bow on the 30th birthday present of @labyrinththeater by reading a play we first premiered 23 years ago. A play that has given me a multitude of life changing/affirming gifts. None bigger than so many amazingly beautiful people I’m lucky enough to still call friends.  Like with all great works of art, its profound impact on countless of people knows no boundaries. Thanks to the audience for showing up BIG TIME last night, and ALL who worked on and off stage the past week, to help celebrate LABs 30th anniversary! Pa’ lante!! HEART FULL 🤎

The LAST first day of school pic😳Go get ‘em, Clemente 💪🏽🤎🙌🏽🤎💪🏽

We first met in a NYC black box theater 25 yrs ago. We instantly connected, we broke down, we helped each other back up…and even, occasionally, soared. 
Watching you soar, Ron, made me so happy cuz it was earned. You rose from the ashes of life’s cruelties multiple times. And with every “second chance” given, you were determined to learn how to reach deeper/higher levels of existence. It was thrilling to see the evolving life-force propelling you forward.
You lived lifetimes to the max. You played the shit out of the hands of cards you were dealt. You were a marvel. I’m going to miss you tremendously.
Watching you with Jasmine, whenever you spoke of your beautiful angel Jaz, you taught me how limitless a father’s love is. Your cool cat style lit the hearts of everyone in every room you walked into. Your childlike awe of everything was a wonder to witness. Your infectious laugh tickled even the jaded ones. Your tireless work ethic & respect for the craft inspired every scene partner lucky enough to share the stage/screen with you. 
I was one of the lucky ones. LAB was one of the lucky ones. One of my biggest life lessons happened to be shared with you during rehearsals. Phil told us that, in order for us to truly go to vicious hate required of our characters, it was of the utmost importance that we (as partners, as humans) needed to unmistakably always LOVE each other more. We could only deliver, receive, and ultimately surrender to the hate if, and only if, the love was clearly underneath it all.
Cephas and I didn’t for a sec take that note lightly. We committed to it as if our lives depended on it. The bond was cemented so securely that, every time we’d see each other over the next 20 years, it felt as if we were hanging out in between shows…as if 20 years ago was just yesterday. Maybe it was no accident that the last time I hugged you goodbye 3 Sundays ago was in a blackbox theater where we gathered to read the beginning of 3 new plays by Stephen. The love never faded. It will never go away. Thank you, Cephas, for all the blessings true friendship can provide. Thank you for always flowing with grace, sincerity, openness, dignity, and kindness. 🤎RIPOWER🕊️

@americanfictionmovie opens today!
This miracle of a movie is rare. Making any movie is extremely challenging. Finding the resources to make one with this story at its core, in full support of @cordjefferson authentic vision, was beyond challenging. It is one of the many reasons we don’t get to see these kinds of films. It was only going to be made on a modest budget, in 26 days, and on the shoulders of every single beautiful person in front and behind the cameras…with truly selfless communal  spirit.
One of the many things it is “about” is community. 
Beginning this weekend,  I hope you can find some respite from today’s trying times in the entertaining company of Monk and The Ellison family and watch it the old-fashioned way, in a movie theater sharing tears & laughter with others,
and prove that these types of stories/movies shouldn’t be the exception but more of the norm.
Now In select cities; expanding more beginning 12/22 (tix link in bio)
